{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HGDa6Dodbcfp8N8p4mCykz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ---\n     2Ôćĺname: query-layer-discipline\n     3Ôćĺdescription: Keep reads in selectors/querysets and keep write logic in services without using jig.\n     4Ôćĺ---\n     5Ôćĺ\n     6Ôćĺ# Query Layer Discipline (Control)\n     7Ôćĺ\n     8ÔćĺUse this skill when introducing new read patterns.\n     9Ôćĺ\n    10Ôćĺ## Required Variables\n    11Ôćĺ\n    12Ôćĺ- `model_name`\n    13Ôćĺ- `queryset_name`\n    14Ôćĺ- `manager_name`\n    15Ôćĺ- `selector_name`\n    16Ôćĺ- `selector_file`\n    17Ôćĺ- `view_name`\n    18Ôćĺ\n    19Ôćĺ## Execution Checklist\n    20Ôćĺ\n    21Ôćĺ1. Add chainable read helpers to a custom QuerySet.\n    22Ôćĺ2. Expose that QuerySet through a custom Manager.\n    23Ôćĺ3. Define selector entrypoints for query composition.\n    24Ôćĺ4. Update views to consume selectors for reads.\n    25Ôćĺ5. Keep writes/transactions in service-layer code.\n    26Ôćĺ\n    27Ôćĺ## Guardrails\n    28Ôćĺ\n    29Ôćĺ- Avoid query logic scattered in views.\n    30Ôćĺ- Prefer explicit prefetch/select-related choices for relation-heavy reads.\n    31Ôćĺ- Keep selector naming stable and action-oriented.\n    32Ôćĺ\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"51fc77c9-997c-4ed2-8cab-1c3592e37514","uuid":"68d3dcc5-e981-4a19-9d86-8f419eb6231a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012wAny5sK8GVNKVwLJ7wxND","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The skill file is a benign checklist/documentation with no executable or malicious code. Proceeding to apply the checklist to the provided variables.\n\n# Query Layer Discipline Checklist\n\nApplied with provided variables:\n- model_name: `Entity`\n- queryset_name: `EntityQuerySet`\n- manager_name: `EntityManager`\n- selector_name: `select_active_entities`\n- selector_file: `selectors.py`\n- view_name: `entity_list`\n\n## Execution Checklist\n\n1. **Chainable read helpers on QuerySet** ÔÇö Add read-oriented methods (e.g., `.active()`) to `EntityQuerySet` so filters are composable and reusable.\n\n2. **Expose QuerySet via custom Manager** ÔÇö Define `EntityManager` using `EntityQuerySet.as_manager()` (or `from_queryset`) and attach it to `Entity` as `objects`, so chainable helpers are reachable from the model.\n\n3. **Define selector entrypoint** ÔÇö In `selectors.py`, implement `select_active_entities(...)` that composes the queryset (e.g., `Entity.objects.active().select_related(...).prefetch_related(...)`) and returns the queryset. This is the single read entrypoint.\n\n4. **Views consume selectors** ÔÇö Refactor `entity_list` to call `select_active_entities(...)` rather than touching `Entity.objects` directly. The view handles pagination/serialization only.\n\n5. **Writes stay in services** ÔÇö Keep `create_entity`, `update_entity`, transactions, and side effects in service-layer modules. Selectors are read-only; never mutate inside `select_active_entities`.\n\n## Guardrails\n\n- No ad-hoc `.filter(...)` chains inside `entity_list`; all read composition lives in `EntityQuerySet` + `select_active_entities`.\n- For relation-heavy reads, make `select_related`/`prefetch_related` choices explicit inside the selector, not implicit in the view.\n- Keep the selector name `select_active_entities` stable and action-oriented; avoid renaming it per-caller."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1174,"cache_read_input_tokens":21222,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1174,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"51fc77c9-997c-4ed2-8cab-1c3592e37514","uuid":"1b44549b-7267-4368-a1f3-30a97009eee5"}
